###Dataset Description

This data is available at http://ftq.mdps.gov.qa:8088/.

In June 2017, a coalition of Arab countries led by the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates, Bahrain, Egypt, as well as Djibouti, imposed a historic economic and diplomatic blockade on Qatar, marking the beginning of the Qatar-Gulf crisis. Qatar was forced to comply with a list of thirteen demands from the coalition, including the closure of Doha's Al Jazeera news channel and to cease its support for various regional Islamist groups. At the time of compiling this data, the blockade was still in place, though Qatar appeared to have been coping with the crisis well. The blockade ended in January 2021.

### Content

This is a balanced dataset of every single thing Qatar imported from 2015 - 2018, from hat pegs to cow milk.

### Inspiration

How exactly did a tiny country withstand a blockade from its biggest trading partners?
title: Qatar Trade Data
subtitle: All imports into Qatar, 2015-2018
